{
  "texts": [
    "In 2018, the LAMOST telescope (Cui et al, 2012; Luo et al, 2012) initiated a dedicated time-domain spectroscopic survey project.",
    "This time-domain survey project is part of the Medium-Resolution Spectroscopic Survey (MRS) of LAMOST, with a spectral resolution power (λ/∆λ) of about 7500 (Liu et al, 2020).",
    "Each MRS spectrum has two observational bands, the red band (about 6300-6800 Å) and the blue band (about 4950-5350 Å), and the Hα line (vacuum wavelength: 6564.614 Å; Stoughton et al 2002) is well covered by the red band of MRS.",
    "Thus the time-domain spectral data of the Hα line are available in the recent data releases of LAMOST, which provides an opportunity to study stellar Hα variability (He et al, 2021).",
    "In this work, we investigate the variability of Hα chromospheric activity of solar-like stars based on the time-domain data of MRS."
  ]
}